A(x) = 2h \sqrt{r^2 -(x-r)^2}
V=\int_0^{2r} 2h \sqrt{r^2 -(x-r)^2}dx
\int_0^{2r} 2h \sqrt{r^2 -(x-r)^2}dx = \pi r^2 h
V= \pi r^2 h
(x-r) = r \sin\theta
x = r + r \sin\theta
\mathrm{dx}=r\cos\theta \rm{d}\theta
x= 0
-r = r\sin\theta
\theta = -\frac{\pi}{2}
x =2r
r=r\sin\theta
\theta = \frac{\pi}{2}
x=a\sin\theta
dx=a\cos\theta\,d\theta
\int\sqrt{a^2-x^2}\,dx
